---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Changelog — SundayRec"
  description="Release notes and version history for SundayRec"
>
  <header class="bg-[#194280] py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <img src="/images/sundayrec_primary_gull-paa-blaa.svg" alt="SundayRec" class="w-10 h-10" />
        <span class="font-bold text-lg text-white">SundayRec</span>
      </a>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-white mb-2">Changelog</h1>
      <p class="text-blue-300 text-sm">Release notes for every version of SundayRec</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">

      <!-- v4.6.0 -->
      <article class="mb-16">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="bg-[#F0BB47] text-[#194280] font-bold text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">v4.6.0</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">May 2026</span>
          <span class="text-xs bg-green-100 text-green-700 font-semibold px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Latest</span>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold text-[#194280] mb-6">Schedule, setup and usability improvements</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8">

          <section>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-[#194280] text-lg mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#F0BB47] inline-block"></span>
              Schedule page
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed pl-4">
              <li>Calendar is now shown at the top of the tab so you always see the full week at a glance</li>
              <li>Advanced options (silence detection, split, reminder, manual max length) are collapsed by default and can be revealed with a single click — the page is much less cluttered for new users</li>
              <li>Fixed a bug where calendar day cells would jump out of position when resizing the window</li>
              <li>Removed iCal export (was incomplete and unused)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-[#194280] text-lg mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#F0BB47] inline-block"></span>
              Setup wizard
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed pl-4">
              <li>You can now choose any day of the week for your weekly recording — not only Sunday. Default remains Sunday at 11:00</li>
              <li>Day picker with all seven days lets you set up a recurring service on Monday, Wednesday, Saturday, or any other day</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-[#194280] text-lg mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#F0BB47] inline-block"></span>
              Home screen
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed pl-4">
              <li>Date and time merged into a single "Time" column in the recording history table — less horizontal clutter</li>
              <li>VU meter scale simplified to "Silent" and "Max" labels instead of technical dB numbers</li>
              <li>History section renamed from "History" to "Latest recordings"</li>
              <li>Maintenance actions (delete errors, remove missing files) moved into a ⋯ overflow menu to keep the interface clean</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-[#194280] text-lg mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#F0BB47] inline-block"></span>
              Settings
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed pl-4">
              <li>Volume slider now uses a neutral fill color instead of distracting green/yellow/red zones</li>
              <li>Sample rate descriptions updated to explain real-world use: 44.1 kHz = "Music, CD &amp; podcasts", 48 kHz = "Video, Zoom &amp; broadcast equipment"</li>
              <li>Audio source tab renamed from "Audio source" to "Audio" — shorter and more direct</li>
              <li>Enhancements (compressor, limiter) merged into the main Audio card instead of a separate card — fewer clicks to reach everything</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h3 class="font-bold text-[#194280] text-lg mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-[#F0BB47] inline-block"></span>
              Security &amp; reliability
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed pl-4">
              <li>Fixed a path traversal vulnerability in the editor's sidecar-file read/write — files outside the audio directory can no longer be accessed</li>
              <li>Fixed a potential command injection in the ffmpeg audio filter chain (channel numbers are now strictly clamped to integers 0–31)</li>
              <li>Tightened validation when importing a settings profile — malformed slot times and invalid date formats are rejected</li>
              <li>Auto-delete now correctly awaits file deletion before updating history, preventing orphaned entries</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

        </div>
      </article>

      <hr class="border-gray-100 mb-16" />

      <!-- v4.5.x and earlier -->
      <article class="mb-16 opacity-70">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 font-bold text-sm px-3 py-1 rounded-full">v4.5.x</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Earlier 2026</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm">
          Audio engine rebuilt in the main process (ffmpeg subprocess) for crash isolation, multi-channel device support,
          compressor and limiter, FLAC/AAC/WAV output, EQ, and the waveform editor with trim/fade.
        </p>
      </article>

    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="bg-[#0f2a54] py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 flex flex-wrap gap-6 text-sm text-blue-300">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">← Back to home</a>
      <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Privacy Policy</a>
      <a href="/terms" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Terms of Service</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>
